b'' b'i recently corrected the resolution on my sparcstation by changing' b'/usr/lib/x11/xdm/xservers from:' b':0 local /usr/bin/x11/x -ar1 -dpi b'to:' b':0 local /usr/bin/x11/x -ar1 -dpi b'' b'i determined that my 1152x900 monitor was dpi by measuring the' b'active screen area and dividing by resolution.' b'' b'however, this has caused my application fonts to behave strangely.' b'after some research, i believe this is caused by my applications' b'requesting fonts by family, weight, slant, and pointsize. i believe' b'that x is grabbing the first font on the path with these characteristics' b'and displaying it. since i have only 75dpi and 100dpi fonts on my' b'path, the results are inaccurate. i do have some speedo fonts, but' b'not for the family i am using (helvetica).' b'' b'i think this is incorrect. the fonts should always be provided in the' b'resolution of the display. this never seems to happen unless you' b'explicitly request fonts by xres and yres! this is true of both the' b'scaleable and bitmapped fonts! for instance, the command' b'' b"xfd -fn '-bitstream-charter-*-*-*-*-*-240-*-*-*-*-*-*'" b'' b'will invoke a 75dpi font (despite the fact that this is a speedo font).' b'' b'the command' b'' b"xfd -fn '-adobe-courier-*-*-*-*-*-240-*-*-*-*-*-*'" b'' b'will invoke a 75dpi font or a 100dpi font (depending on my font path).' b'despite the fact that x knows my display is dpi, and that it can' b'generate an 85dpi font for me! unless i my applications specifies a' b'resolution, x appears to pick a stupid default.' b'' b'is this a bug? is it a feature? if so, why? is there anything i can' b'do to get around this problem? people have suggested that i lie about' b'my resolution, and specify a single font path or not both).' b'this would at least make my app consistent, but i like being able to' b'look at rulers that appear in my paint application and say: "yup, thats' b'an inch". anyone have a set of 85dpi bitmapped fonts i can use?' b'' b'system info:' b'sun sparc w/32 mb, sunos b'' b'xdpyinfo:' b'version number: b'vendor string: mit x consortium' b'vendor release number: b'screen b'dimensions: 1152x900 pixels (348x272 millimeters)' b'resolution: 85x85 dots per inch' b'' b'xset q font path:' b'/usr/lib/x11/fonts/misc/,/usr/lib/x11/fonts/speedo/,/usr/lib/x11/fonts/100dpi/,/usr/lib/x11/fonts/75dpi/' b'' b'--' b'applications architect, applications technology group, applications division' b'oracle corporation, redwood shores, ca 